We found that the standard current-voltage (I-V) rela-
tion, based on Ohm's law and the Nernst equation, is
inadequate to describe all of Rorsman and Trube's (Rors-
man and Trube, 1986) data for the Ca2` current. We
obtained an improved fit to the experimental I-V curve by
multiplying the current by a reverse sigmoidal factor,

1 + exp [(V- Vh)/Sh]'

