We choose At so that this probability is <0.1, which
assures that the probability of two openings is negligible.
To decide if a channel closing occurs in our simulations, we
use a random number generator to obtain a random
variable, X, chosen from a uniform distribution on the
interval [0, 1]. If X < No * At/Tr, we increment Nc and
decrement No by 1; otherwise we do nothing. We then
